{"id": "duc04-testb-23:6#20", "contents": "The International Monetary Fund has provided bailout packages totaling $137 billion since the financial crisis began in Thailand 15 months ago and subsequently spread to Russia. The U.S. administration, aware of the potential impact of a Latin American recession on the United States, has actively supported the IMF and the World Bank in their efforts to assist Brazil after it was hit by investor flight. The final declaration is set to be approved at the summit in the port city in northern Portugal on Sunday."}
